e developments. Being Boys will be of interest to scholars and students across the humanities and social sciences and is also relevant to those teaching and studying in the fields of child development, education, and youth and community studies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aTeenage boysxSocial conditionsy20th century. 0aWorking class menxSocial conditionsy20th century. 0aYoung menxSocial conditionsy20th century. 4amanchesterhive variable pricing textbooks. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Children's Studies.2bisacsh  aBoys.  aBritish history.  aLeisure.  aadolescence.  ainterwar.  amasculinity.  asexuality.  ayouth.1 aTebbutt, Melanie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez9783111283630oZDB-23-MUP40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526130730423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526130730/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-MUPc1986d2013